Understanding Company product requirements

Companys automated product generates a list of xyz coordinates for trimming retainers and aligners.

Resolution: <>The dental arch should have at minimum 100k triangles or be around 5MB for an STL file. Meshes with less resolution will yield results that are not as smooth.

 Orientation: <>The arch can be in any orientation. The output will be created in reference to the orientation of the input arch unless the user optionally selects to use Companys automated trim & base afterward which can align the base to z=0 for immediate 3D printing.

 Quality: The arch should not have excess or large artifacts and also should not contain significant occlusions (see below). Arches that have brackets with wires have unreliable performance, however arches brackets and no wires are acceptable input, and can optionally be removed using Companys automated bracket removal product. Arches with small holes and normal artifacts will still yield a good quality trimline. Base: We are unable to process pre-based models.

Example cases

This arch is a good input example. It has enough gum area to trim from, teeth are well defined, no excess artifacts.

This arch is also an example that would work well for trim base.

This is an example of an arch with excess artifacts. Especially when the artifacts intersect the desired trimline, we cannot consistently create a valid output for these types of input.

Since this has a hollow base, we currently cannot generate a trimline for these, but were working on adding support for this.
